Package pqueue.priorityqueues

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PriorityQueue<T>
    A PriorityQueue is an extension of a classic FIFO queue.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LinearPriorityQueue<T>
    LinearPriorityQueue is a PriorityQueue implemented as a linear Collection of common FIFOQueues, where the FIFOQueues themselves hold objects with the same priority (in the order they were inserted).
    MinHeapPriorityQueue<T>
    MinHeapPriorityQueue is a PriorityQueue implemented using a MinHeap.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EmptyPriorityQueueException
    A Exception thrown by PriorityQueue-based data structures when the queue is empty.
